<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6896&amp;p=66643#p66643"><![CDATA[
Lua scripts are for the emulator they run inside, and give enhancements to the emulator.<br />They don't do any ASM hacks.  Just peeks and pokes.<br /><br />Porting it to a cartridge is about as reasonable as porting an MP3 replacement music system.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Tue Aug 24, 2010 6:32 am</p><hr />
